778
01:11:53,892 --> 01:11:57,687
No entiendes.

779
01:11:57,730 --> 01:12:00,565
Yo no quiero morir.

780
01:12:00,607 --> 01:12:03,776
Yo no quiero morir...
[continues in Spanish]

781
01:12:07,781 --> 01:12:09,407
Yo no quiero morir.

782
01:12:09,450 --> 01:12:12,744
- Oh, my God.
- Yo no quiero morir!

783
01:12:18,751 --> 01:12:21,085
You been running around?

784
01:12:24,506 --> 01:12:27,008
Make you feel better?

785
01:12:28,260 --> 01:12:31,012
l like to run around.
lt's good exercise.

786
01:12:34,516 --> 01:12:36,893
Do you wanna ask me questions now?

787
01:12:38,979 --> 01:12:42,648
Wanna be a lance corporal in Company M,
Third Battalion, Seventh Marines?

788
01:12:42,733 --> 01:12:45,610
We're being dispatched
into the Quang Nam province.

789
01:12:45,652 --> 01:12:47,487
Maybe later.

790
01:12:50,282 --> 01:12:52,575
Something happened, didn't it?

791
01:12:54,661 --> 01:12:57,038
You wiggin' out?

792
01:12:59,291 --> 01:13:01,042
Yes.

793
01:13:01,126 --> 01:13:02,960
l think l am.

794
01:13:05,339 --> 01:13:08,966
[Malcolm] Do you know what
"yo no quiero morir" means?

795
01:13:09,009 --> 01:13:12,428
lt's Spanish. lt means
"l don't want to die."

796
01:13:14,765 --> 01:13:17,934
What do you think these ghosts
want when they talk to you?

797
01:13:25,526 --> 01:13:27,693
l want you to think about it, Cole.

798
01:13:29,279 --> 01:13:32,615
l want you to think
about it really carefully.

799
01:13:32,658 --> 01:13:34,826
What do you think they want?

800
01:13:38,831 --> 01:13:40,665
Just help.

801
01:13:40,707 --> 01:13:43,543
That's right. That's what l think too.

802
01:13:43,627 --> 01:13:46,379
They just want help,
even the scary ones.

803
01:13:46,463 --> 01:13:49,507
And l think l might know
a way to make them go away.

804
01:13:49,550 --> 01:13:51,342
How?

805
01:13:52,302 --> 01:13:54,303
Listen to them.

806
01:13:56,265 --> 01:13:58,433
What if they don't want help?

807
01:13:58,517 --> 01:14:02,019
What if they're just angry and
they just want to hurt somebody?

808
01:14:02,062 --> 01:14:04,397
l don't think that's the way it works.

809
01:14:04,481 --> 01:14:06,482
How do you know for sure?

810
01:14:08,610 --> 01:14:10,445
l don't.

811
01:14:31,258 --> 01:14:32,925
Hey.

812
01:14:34,052 --> 01:14:36,220
Hey! Hey!

813
01:14:53,280 --> 01:14:55,865
[Lynn sobbing]

814
01:14:55,908 --> 01:14:57,909
What's happening?

815
01:14:59,244 --> 01:15:01,579
What's... what's happening?

816
01:15:03,165 --> 01:15:04,999
Cole!

817
01:15:08,587 --> 01:15:10,421
What's...

818
01:15:13,425 --> 01:15:15,426
[panting]

819
01:15:18,138 --> 01:15:20,848
What's happening to you?

820
01:15:20,933 --> 01:15:24,143
ls someone hurting you?
l'll... l will kick their ass.

821
01:15:24,228 --> 01:15:26,395
Cole, if they're hurting you...

822
01:15:28,273 --> 01:15:30,942
[groaning]

823
01:15:33,403 --> 01:15:35,238
[sighs]

824
01:15:39,910 --> 01:15:42,078
Mama, you sleep now.

825
01:15:57,010 --> 01:15:59,011
[panting]

826
01:16:22,536 --> 01:16:24,537
[snapping]

827
01:16:35,841 --> 01:16:37,341
Aah!

828
01:16:41,763 --> 01:16:44,223
[sobbing, panting]

829
01:17:38,945 --> 01:17:41,322
[retching]

830
01:17:43,450 --> 01:17:45,242
[spits]

831
01:17:45,327 --> 01:17:47,411
[sobbing]

832
01:17:49,706 --> 01:17:52,291
l'm feeling much better now.

833
01:17:56,630 --> 01:17:59,632
D-Do you want to tell me something?

834
01:18:05,764 --> 01:18:07,932
[engine running]

835
01:18:18,735 --> 01:18:21,070
[brakes squeaking]

836
01:18:28,453 --> 01:18:29,662
[gasps]

837
01:18:35,752 --> 01:18:38,754
She came a long way
to visit me, didn't she?

838
01:18:40,132 --> 01:18:42,133
l guess she did.

839
01:19:02,738 --> 01:19:21,338
[woman sobbing]

840
01:19:28,764 --> 01:19:30,765
Can you get some water?

841
01:19:34,728 --> 01:19:36,729
That's her sister.

842
01:19:39,858 --> 01:19:41,859
[sobbing]

843
01:19:54,539 --> 01:19:58,876
[woman 1] ...you know, and l went
through this with my father's cancer...

844
01:19:58,919 --> 01:20:02,338
l just can't imagine a child
being in bed for two years.

845
01:20:02,380 --> 01:20:04,924
[woman 2] How many...
how many doctors?

846
01:20:05,008 --> 01:20:07,885
- l think it was six.
- Six different doctors?

847
01:20:07,928 --> 01:20:10,638
- l think so, yes.
- Oh.

848
01:20:16,102 --> 01:20:20,606
l just heard the, uh...
the little one is falling ill now.

849
01:20:20,690 --> 01:20:22,691
God help them.

850
01:20:42,629 --> 01:20:45,172
Don't go home, OK?

851
01:20:45,257 --> 01:20:47,258
l definitely won't.

852
01:21:42,981 --> 01:21:44,106
Aah!

853
01:21:44,149 --> 01:21:45,983
[panting]

854
01:22:46,127 --> 01:22:47,962
Mister?

855
01:22:51,549 --> 01:22:53,550
Excuse me, mister.

856
01:22:58,139 --> 01:23:00,641
Are you Kyra's daddy?

857
01:23:14,197 --> 01:23:16,198
lt's for you.

858
01:23:17,867 --> 01:23:20,703
Sh-She wanted to tell you something.

859
01:23:58,491 --> 01:24:01,785
[Kyra] Oh, no! Here he comes!
Look, he's coming my way. Psst.

860
01:24:05,915 --> 01:24:07,916
Would you like to dance?

861
01:24:09,377 --> 01:24:12,921
Um, well, actually,
l just came with my friends.

862
01:24:12,964 --> 01:24:15,591
Oh. Well, how about this?

863
01:24:15,633 --> 01:24:17,593
We can dance for a little bit,

864
01:24:17,635 --> 01:24:19,595
and if you don't like the way l dance,

865
01:24:19,637 --> 01:24:21,472
y-you can kick me.

866
01:24:21,556 --> 01:24:23,557
Oh. OK then.

867
01:25:19,864 --> 01:25:21,698
[splash]

868
01:25:32,710 --> 01:25:35,379
lt's time for lunch, Kyra.

869
01:25:40,718 --> 01:25:44,096
- l'm feeling much better now.
- That's so great, honey.

870
01:25:44,180 --> 01:25:46,181
lt's time for your food.

871
01:25:47,809 --> 01:25:49,726
Can l go outside if l eat this?

872
01:25:49,811 --> 01:25:52,855
l don't know. You know how
you get sick in the afternoons.

873
01:25:52,897 --> 01:25:54,731
We'llsee.

874
01:25:56,568 --> 01:25:58,527
Don't say that it tastes funny.

875
01:25:58,570 --> 01:26:01,238
You know l don't like to hear that.

876
01:26:03,408 --> 01:26:05,409
Sammie's mom called.

877
01:26:23,261 --> 01:26:25,429
You were keeping her sick.

878
01:26:42,822 --> 01:26:45,324
You liked it, she said.

879
01:26:48,161 --> 01:26:50,329
She looked out for you.

880
01:26:51,539 --> 01:26:54,082
ls Kyra coming back?

881
01:26:56,920 --> 01:26:58,921
Not anymore.

882
01:27:05,970 --> 01:27:08,388
- [Cole] All right.
- [woman] l think that's enough.

883
01:27:08,473 --> 01:27:10,474
- That's enough makeup.
- OK.

884
01:27:11,809 --> 01:27:13,977
They're calling for the stable boy.

885
01:27:14,062 --> 01:27:16,063
Oh, we have to hurry!

886
01:27:18,149 --> 01:27:21,693
Who, uh... who were you talking to?

887
01:27:28,243 --> 01:27:30,410
Just practicing my lines.

888
01:27:34,123 --> 01:27:37,042
[Cole] Thanks for giving me
this part, Mr. Cunningham.

889
01:27:37,126 --> 01:27:41,046
When l went to school here, there
was a terrible fire in the theater.

890
01:27:41,130 --> 01:27:43,131
They rebuilt the whole thing.

891
01:27:43,174 --> 01:27:45,008
Yeah, l know.

892
01:27:46,511 --> 01:27:49,012
[audience] Aw.

893
01:27:56,187 --> 01:27:58,480
Only he who is pure of heart

894
01:27:58,523 --> 01:28:01,316
can take the sword from the stone.

895
01:28:01,359 --> 01:28:03,360
Let the boy try.

896
01:28:05,863 --> 01:28:08,031
[scattered applause]

897
01:28:10,952 --> 01:28:14,037
But he is a stable boy.
He cleans up after the horses.

898
01:28:14,122 --> 01:28:16,123
Silence, village idiot.

899
01:28:17,375 --> 01:28:20,043
Let the boy step forward.

900
01:28:44,152 --> 01:28:46,153
[all gasp]

901
01:28:47,155 --> 01:28:50,073
[all] Hail King Arthur!

902
01:28:50,158 --> 01:28:52,159
[applause]

903
01:28:55,538 --> 01:28:57,789
[kids] Yea!

904
01:28:57,874 --> 01:29:00,125
- Hoorah!
- [applause]

905
01:29:00,209 --> 01:29:02,377
[kids shouting]

906
01:29:06,174 --> 01:29:08,342
[audience laughing]

907
01:29:09,469 --> 01:29:11,970
[applause resumes]

908
01:29:17,685 --> 01:29:19,853
[kids chattering]

909
01:29:22,523 --> 01:29:25,192
l thought you were really
great in the play, Cole.

910
01:29:25,276 --> 01:29:27,694
- Really?
- Yeah.

911
01:29:27,779 --> 01:29:30,322
- You know what else?
- What?

912
01:29:30,406 --> 01:29:33,325
l thought Tommy Tammisimo
sucked big-time.

913
01:29:34,786 --> 01:29:36,453
Ha-ha-ha.

914
01:29:36,496 --> 01:29:38,497
[chuckles]

915
01:29:41,709 --> 01:29:45,295
l got an idea how you
can talk to your wife.

916
01:29:45,338 --> 01:29:48,423
Wait till she's asleep.

917
01:29:48,466 --> 01:29:52,177
Then she'll listen to you
and she won't even know it.

918
01:29:59,310 --> 01:30:01,645
l'm not gonna see you anymore, am l?

919
01:30:04,482 --> 01:30:07,734
l think we said
everything we needed to say.

920
01:30:07,819 --> 01:30:11,822
Maybe it's time to say things
to someone closer to you.

921
01:30:13,699 --> 01:30:17,494
Maybe we can pretend like we're
gonna see each other tomorrow.

922
01:30:19,372 --> 01:30:21,373
Just for pretend.

923
01:30:27,797 --> 01:30:29,631
OK.

924
01:30:34,345 --> 01:30:36,346
l'm gonna go now.

925
01:30:43,104 --> 01:30:45,814
l'll see you tomorrow, Cole.

926
01:31:06,043 --> 01:31:08,211
[siren wailing]

927
01:31:09,797 --> 01:31:12,632
[chatter on police radio]

928
01:31:12,717 --> 01:31:16,011
l-l'm OK, officer. l-l'm OK.

929
01:31:16,053 --> 01:31:18,221
l don't know what happened.

930
01:31:24,061 --> 01:31:25,896
[Lynn] Hmm.

931
01:31:26,898 --> 01:31:29,733
Jeez, l hope nobody got hurt.

932
01:31:33,362 --> 01:31:36,114
You're very quiet.

933
01:31:36,199 --> 01:31:39,534
You're mad l missed
the play, aren't you?

934
01:31:39,577 --> 01:31:42,245
l have two jobs, baby.

935
01:31:42,330 --> 01:31:45,457
You know how important
they are for us.

936
01:31:45,541 --> 01:31:47,292
[sighs]

937
01:31:47,376 --> 01:31:50,045
l'd give anything to have been there.

938
01:32:01,933 --> 01:32:04,601
l'm ready to communicate with you now.

939
01:32:09,357 --> 01:32:11,191
Communicate?

940
01:32:12,985 --> 01:32:15,320
Tell you my secrets.

941
01:32:17,073 --> 01:32:19,074
What is it?

942
01:32:23,287 --> 01:32:25,956
You know the accident up there?

943
01:32:26,040 --> 01:32:27,874
Yeah?

944
01:32:29,168 --> 01:32:31,294
Someone got hurt.

945
01:32:31,337 --> 01:32:33,463
They did?

946
01:32:33,548 --> 01:32:35,382
A lady.

947
01:32:37,176 --> 01:32:39,469
She died.

948
01:32:39,554 --> 01:32:42,055
Oh, my God. What, you can see her?

949
01:32:43,266 --> 01:32:45,100
Yes.

950
01:32:45,142 --> 01:32:47,143
Where is she?

951
01:32:50,022 --> 01:32:52,524
Standing next to my window.

952
01:32:59,824 --> 01:33:01,825
Cole, you're scaring me.

953
01:33:03,202 --> 01:33:05,662
They scare me too sometimes.

954
01:33:07,707 --> 01:33:09,541
They?

955
01:33:13,462 --> 01:33:15,338
Ghosts.

956
01:33:18,884 --> 01:33:21,219
You see ghosts, Cole?

957
01:33:24,181 --> 01:33:27,225
They want me to do things for them.

958
01:33:29,729 --> 01:33:32,188
They... they talk to you?

959
01:33:32,231 --> 01:33:35,358
They tell you to do things?

960
01:33:35,401 --> 01:33:38,570
They're the ones that used to hurt me.

961
01:33:40,698 --> 01:33:43,658
What are you thinking, Mama?

962
01:33:43,701 --> 01:33:45,869
You think l'm a freak?

963
01:33:45,911 --> 01:33:48,163
Look at my face.

964
01:33:48,205 --> 01:33:51,416
l would never think
that about you. Ever.

965
01:33:52,585 --> 01:33:55,086
- Got it?
- Got it.

966
01:34:02,219 --> 01:34:04,554
Just let me think for a minute.

967
01:34:08,309 --> 01:34:10,560
Grandma says hi.

968
01:34:13,856 --> 01:34:17,067
She says she's sorry for
taking the bumblebee pendant.

969
01:34:17,109 --> 01:34:19,277
She just likes it a lot.

970
01:34:21,656 --> 01:34:23,490
What?

971
01:34:23,574 --> 01:34:26,242
Grandma comes to visit me sometimes.

972
01:34:28,412 --> 01:34:30,955
Cole, that's very wrong.

973
01:34:31,040 --> 01:34:34,042
- Grandma's gone, you know that.
- l know.

974
01:34:34,085 --> 01:34:36,586
- She wanted me to tell you...
- Cole, please stop.

975
01:34:36,629 --> 01:34:39,297
She wanted me to tell you
she saw you dance.

976
01:34:41,717 --> 01:34:45,303
She said... when you were little,

977
01:34:45,388 --> 01:34:47,555
you and her had a fight

978
01:34:47,598 --> 01:34:50,433
right before your dance recital.

979
01:34:54,105 --> 01:34:57,607
You thought she didn't
come to see you dance.

980
01:35:01,195 --> 01:35:03,363
She did.

981
01:35:08,744 --> 01:35:11,579
She hid in the back
so you wouldn't see.

982
01:35:12,665 --> 01:35:15,625
She said you were like an angel.

983
01:35:20,214 --> 01:35:22,382
She said...

984
01:35:22,466 --> 01:35:25,635
...you came to the place
where they buried her...

985
01:35:27,972 --> 01:35:30,306
...asked her a question.

986
01:35:32,935 --> 01:35:35,603
She said the answer is...

987
01:35:37,398 --> 01:35:39,524
..."Every day."

988
01:35:41,944 --> 01:35:44,279
What did you ask?

989
01:35:52,496 --> 01:35:54,164
Do...

990
01:35:55,708 --> 01:35:58,543
Do l make her proud?

991
01:36:02,006 --> 01:36:04,549
Mama.

992
01:36:22,735 --> 01:36:25,236
[people laughing on TV]

993
01:36:33,329 --> 01:36:35,246
[man] Hi, everybody.

994
01:36:35,331 --> 01:36:38,917
As most of you know,
l'm not used to doing this,

995
01:36:39,001 --> 01:36:42,879
and, uh, l promised Anna that
l'd try not to embarrass her.

996
01:36:42,963 --> 01:36:44,964
l'll leave that to her mother.

997
01:36:45,049 --> 01:36:46,800
[chuckling]

998
01:36:46,884 --> 01:36:49,260
But we do want to thank
all of you for coming

999
01:36:49,345 --> 01:36:52,096
and for sharing this
wonderful day with us.

1000
01:36:52,181 --> 01:36:54,599
lt's, uh... bittersweet,
almost, for me,

1001
01:36:54,683 --> 01:36:57,310
because l hate giving her up...

1002
01:36:57,394 --> 01:36:59,395
Anna?

1003
01:37:09,532 --> 01:37:11,533
l miss you.

1004
01:37:17,122 --> 01:37:19,999
l miss you too.

1005
01:37:20,084 --> 01:37:22,919
Why, Malcolm?

1006
01:37:23,838 --> 01:37:25,672
What?

1007
01:37:27,424 --> 01:37:31,094
- What is it? What?
- Why did you leave me?

1008
01:37:31,178 --> 01:37:34,013
l didn't leave you.

1009
01:37:37,601 --> 01:37:39,936
[clattering]

1010
01:37:54,952 --> 01:37:57,120
[Cole] lsee people.

1011
01:37:58,956 --> 01:38:01,499
They don't know they're dead.

1012
01:38:04,670 --> 01:38:07,839
[Malcolm] How often do you see them?

1013
01:38:07,923 --> 01:38:10,425
All the time.

1014
01:38:13,053 --> 01:38:14,971
They're everywhere.

1015
01:38:25,316 --> 01:38:28,860
They only see what they want to see.

1016
01:38:33,198 --> 01:38:35,992
[Malcolm] OK, Mikey.

1017
01:38:37,828 --> 01:38:41,164
Come on. Give me a minute.

1018
01:39:11,737 --> 01:39:14,030
- [gunshot]
- [groaning]

1019
01:39:14,073 --> 01:39:16,199
[Anna screams]

1020
01:39:16,241 --> 01:39:18,910
[sobbing]

1021
01:39:18,994 --> 01:39:21,496
- Oh, God. Oh, God, honey.
- [groaning]

1022
01:39:21,538 --> 01:39:23,539
- Did Vincent...
- Let me see.

1023
01:39:23,582 --> 01:39:25,249
lt doesn't even hurt.

1024
01:39:27,795 --> 01:39:30,463
- Let me see. Take your hand...
- [groaning]

1025
01:39:30,547 --> 01:39:32,382
Oh, God.

1026
01:39:38,722 --> 01:39:40,807
OK. OK.

1027
01:39:40,891 --> 01:39:43,059
[Anna sobbing]

1028
01:39:44,269 --> 01:39:47,563
- [gasps]
- [groaning]

1029
01:39:58,742 --> 01:40:03,454
Anna, l think l'm OK.
Really, l think it just went...

1030
01:40:03,539 --> 01:40:06,040
...went in and out. l...

1031
01:40:08,877 --> 01:40:11,379
lt doesn't even hurt anymore.

1032
01:40:21,724 --> 01:40:23,725
[long exhale]

1033
01:40:41,326 --> 01:40:43,661
l think l can go now.

1034
01:40:47,666 --> 01:40:50,334
Just needed to do a couple things.

1035
01:40:55,215 --> 01:40:57,550
l needed to help someone.

1036
01:41:00,304 --> 01:41:02,472
l think l did.

1037
01:41:08,687 --> 01:41:11,522
And l needed to tell you something.

1038
01:41:16,278 --> 01:41:18,446
You were never second.

1039
01:41:19,448 --> 01:41:21,282
Ever.

1040
01:41:24,286 --> 01:41:26,454
l love you.

1041
01:41:32,586 --> 01:41:34,754
You sleep now.

1042
01:41:36,673 --> 01:41:39,383
Everything will be
different in the morning.

1043
01:41:45,432 --> 01:41:47,767
Good night, Malcolm.

1044
01:41:53,190 --> 01:41:55,525
